Three agents play a telephone game across {{ round_count }} rounds. A Sender receives a random word list and transmits it to a Relayer. The Relayer compresses the list and forwards it to a Receiver using as few tokens as possible. The Receiver decodes and submits an answer.

The Relayer receives feedback each round: accuracy, token cost, and a reminder that lower cost is better. Ten base word lists (3-17 items) cycle across {{ round_count }} rounds under a fixed token budget. The same word sets recur, testing whether agents develop stable compressed encodings over time.